02/04/2008
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Montenegrin Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic met with EU foreign policy chief Javier Solana in Brussels on Tuesday (April 1st) about relations between Podgorica and the EU and ways to boost regional co-operation. 
"The relationship between Montenegro and the EU is very good," Solana said after the meeting, as he urged the government to keep up the current pace of reforms. 
Djukanovic reiterated that his government is committed to implementing the Stabilisation and Association Agreement signed with the EU in January and to continuing its fight against corruption and organised crime. 
(Vijesti - 02/04/08; Beta, RTCG, Mina - 01/04/08)
